  "title": "Business Development Manager (Oilfield Equipment / OCTG / Steel Trading)",
  "description": "<p>Our client, a reputable global trading company with a strong Japanese roots, specializing in high quality steel products across the energy sector.<br /><br />As part of our strategic expansion, we are seeking a dynamic, driven, and commercially sharp Business Development Manager to strengthen our regional sales presence and build long-term partnerships within the oil & gas market.<br /><strong></strong></p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>As a Business Development Manager, you will play a vital role in expanding our business footprint across Asia. Your responsibilities include:</p><ul><li>Identify, develop, and secure new business opportunities within the oil & gas sector.</li><li>Strengthen and expand relationships with existing customers, distributors, and partners.</li><li>Explore new markets, products, and service offerings to support business expansion plans.</li></ul><ul><li>Work closely with internal teams—including technical, operations, and procurement—to align strategies and deliver customer-focused solutions.</li><li>Prepare commercial proposals, handle contract negotiations, and drive closure of sales opportunities</li><li>Monitor industry trends, competitor activity, and market demand to recommend new product or market entry strategies.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Business, Marketing, Mechanical Engineering, or related field.</li><li>Minimum 5 years of experience in an oilfield service company or in sales of oil & gas equipment/materials.</li><li>Strong technical/product knowledge in  Wellhead & Christmas tree systems, Drill pipes, OCTG, completion tools, drilling fluids, sucker rods, valves, fittings, and steel products</li></ul><p></p>",
